This article is a fact sheet released by the White House Office of the Press Secretary on June 27, 2013. It highlights the United States' support for strengthening democratic institutions, rule of law, and human rights in Sub-Saharan Africa. The US has provided over $292 million in support through the US Department of State and USAID in areas such as supporting civil society and independent media, assisting credible elections and democratic processes, consolidating the rule of law and protecting human rights, partnering to promote open government and transparency, and leveraging technology to revolutionize governance and civic participation. The article provides specific examples of programs and initiatives in various African countries that aim to achieve these goals.